stegan.py
Author: Eugene Ma (edma2)

Dependencies: 
----------------------
PyCrypto (https://www.dlitz.net/software/pycrypto/)
PIL (http://www.pythonware.com/products/pil/)

Description:
----------------------
pystego is a steganographic library for python, which encodes arbitrary streams
of bytes into PNG image files.

Usage:
----------------------
x201:stegan/ master✗ % cat test.py
import sys, Image, getpass
sys.path.append('src')
import stegan

im = Image.open('test/tux.png').convert('RGB')
writer = stegan.Writer(im, 'password')
writer.encode('hello, world')
im.save("test/test.png")

im = Image.open('test/test.png').convert('RGB')
reader = stegan.Reader(im, 'password')
print reader.decode()

x201:stegan/ master✗ % python test.py
hello, world!
